The paper discusses the implementation of deep neural networks, specifically fully-connected and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY). The focus of the paper is on reducing the memory requirements and energy consumption of these networks, which is a common concern in hardware implementation (cs.AR). The proposed solution involves sparsely-connected networks, which is a technique commonly used in neural network optimization (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed solution on popular datasets, which is a common practice in neural network research (cs.NE).
